#Darwin 4087
$info=darwin
$icon=darwin
$data
$bio
Tips and Tricks:


Here is some info on the 
powerups:

Pister, Beas ( Your starting
level ), Basum, Sharru, 
Miseave, Twipet, Dodok, Zugau,
Kues ****, Shasuem, Zugoga,
and Gasharro

Each time you get one of those
power-ups, you go up a level. 
Each time you get hit [or] 
after a short time, you drop
down a level. You start on 
Beas which allows you to get 
hit once without dying (kind,
aren't they?). You can never 
drop below Pister unless you 
get hit.

Now, if you power up to 
Sharru, allow it to drop down 
a level and then get another 
powerup, you reach Laysper. 
This is an evolutionary dead-
end. No amount of power ups 
will get you any further. 
You need to power down and 
power up again.

To get the *beefy* power ups,
go to Kues, and allow a power
down. You then go up this 
ladder: Measa, Malto, Seas,
and Deam (now we're cooking!)

Allow yourself to get hit when
you are Deam - You now become
Black Deam ( mega bat power )
!!!! Excellent !!!


There are plenty of other neat 
touches such as docking with 
some of the bosses. I know 
there was a horizontal stick 
alien which if you shot the 
right number of times drifts 
slowly down the screen. You 
can dock with this to get 
extra firepower.

This means the aliens that 
have extendible poles that 
spring out from their sides. 
Just shoot them until they 
flash, dock with them, and 
you'll get a particularly 
useful upgrade to your bombs.

You can also dock with the 
rectangular aliens ( after you 
have shot them a few times ). 
These appear close to the 
start of the game. It seems 
anything you shoot that then 
drifts slowly down, you can 
dock with (which increases 
the bomb power).


Did you notice the "bird" 
aliens that start at the 
bottom and flap their way up 
the screen ? Well guess what-
you can actually *mutate* with
these. Simply fly over the top 
of them and keep firing. You 
will then mutate into an "eye"
type creature that sprays 
bullets all over.

$end


