Tips and Tricks:


The red sword: If you get all 
the flying swords that attack 
you on the "walking" levels by 
defending them and tapping 
down, you get the red sword. 
If you have it, and you 
repeatedly attack an enemy, 
you will become invincible for 
a while and your armor will be 
replenished.


The golden shield: You pick it 
up on the "walking" levels. It 
does not downgrade from 
missiles like the normal
sheilds do.


You can pick up Irene's sword 
in level 1, and Zaid's mace in 
level 2 (stronger weapon, 
specially useful against 
Agathon and the rolling 
barrels)


You can break all the enemy's 
swords (and Zaid's mace) by 
hitting them constantly.


A tip to defeat Irene: lower 
your shield and she will only 
use low = attacks. Break her 
sword (see above).


**Special trick: How to strip 
Irene's clothes off!

This trick works only (as far 
as I know) on the Japanese 
version (Ohgon no Siro). The 
American version is censored.

After breaking her sword, if 
her shield is not entirely 
broken, break it. Irene, 
unlike the other characters, 
has TWO suits of armor. DO NOT 
KILL HER! Try to remove as 
many parts of the armor as you 
can, throwing careful attacks. 
Focus especially on her 
chestplate and on the... uh...
"thighplate"?. After you've 
done that, defeat her BY 
ATTACKING HER LEGS. She will 
fall on her knees, with her 
sword on her hands against her 
chest. When you pass her, she 
extends her arms towards you 
and... HELLO!

$end

