#Pac Land
$info=pacland,pacland2,pacland
3,paclandm
$icon=pacland
$data
$bio
Tips and Tricks:


Pushing Fire Hydrants, Cactus, 
or Tree Stumps the opposite 
direction you are going will 
give you surprises like a 
Helmet, Invincibility, or 
sometimes a warp! To push an 
item, jump over it, turn 
around, and run into it at 
full speed. Keep running, and 
it will be pushed to the left. 
Some objects can also be 
pushed to the right.

A good example of this is on 
the first set of trees you 
come to after the start. You 
will see a cherry floating 
above your head as you enter 
the woods. Keep running past 
it until you come to a tree 
stump and keep running as 
though you're trying to push 
the stump to the right. Wait 
until the cherry floats just 
past your head then 
continuously hit run and jump 
so that you collect the cherry
plus all the others that 
appear in sequence. Now jump 
over the next tree stump and 
"push" it backwards. You'll 
get a massive score bonus 
(100,000 ?) and get warped 
forward a few levels.

Another example: On the 4th 
level of every trip (with the 
Fairy Shoes) pushing back an 
item will bring out a bunch 
of balloons. One of them is 
worth 7650 and the rest are 
only 100.


Use the Helmet to block the 
little ghosts dropped from 
airplanes and Inky and you'll 
get 300 points for each one. 
Also, if you are in an area 
with airplanes and a Power 
Pellet is nearby, wait until 
a little ghost or 2 are 
dropped and grab the Power 
Pellet and eat little ghosts 
as they are falling (this is 
tough to do). Any ghost you 
eat after the 5th is worth 
7650 points!


Try to collect the "power 
pills" when as many ghosts as 
possible are on screen so 
that you can kill all four 
that move around plus the one 
that constantly "trails" you. 
If you manage to get all four 
plus the "trailing" one LAST, 
a small pacman with the letter 
"L" appears. Jump and catch it 
to get a bonus for the amount 
of time you have remaining, 
and your time reset to full.


You can receive bonus points 
by jumping at a particular 
place at the end of each
level. 
The points received are 
relevant to the vertical 
position of your character 
when the level finishes. This 
works at the end of every 
stage, not just where there 
is a church, e.g. the return 
journey to your "family". The
maximum score for being just 
short of landing is 7650. To 
achieve this, if you are near 
a church, jump when the center 
of your head is horizontally 
level with the rear "wall" of 
the church.

$end

